{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/pulls/692","id":4050122851,"node_id":"PR_kwDOSbOoU87xZ_hj","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/692","diff_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/692.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/692.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/692","number":692,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"E40: CI lint burning down hardcoded natural-language strings (R379)","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"Closes #659 (E40).\n\n## What this does\n\nAdds a CI gate that **burns down** hardcoded user-facing natural-language strings in `src/` (R379), the same way `check-file-size.rs` guards file size. New prose can no longer land in Rust code without either grounding it in `data/seed/*.lino` or explicitly admitting it as tracked debt — and admitted debt can only shrink.\n\n## Commits\n\n1. **`ci(R379): add hardcoded-natural-language burn-down gate`** — the script, the seeded allowlist, CI wiring, and docs.\n2. **`refactor(R379): migrate engine_responses fallbacks to seed`** — the burn-down migration that removes 8 allowlisted rows, proving the loop.\n\n### The gate — `scripts/check-hardcoded-language.rs` (rust-script)\n\nScans every `src/**/*.rs` for user-facing prose string literals using a low-noise **sentence heuristic**: a literal that contains a space, ends in terminal punctuation (`.`/`!`/`?`), and holds at least two real words. Comments, char literals, and single-token trace/event slugs are ignored by construction (a char-level lexer handles normal + raw strings, escapes, and `\\`-newline continuations).\n\nIt **fails the build two ways**, so the inventory can only shrink:\n- a `src/` literal **not** in the allowlist → new debt is blocked;\n- an allowlist row whose literal **no longer occurs** in `src/` → a migrated row must be pruned (keeps the inventory honest).\n\nShips with 9 inline `rust-script --test` unit tests (comment skipping, raw strings, continuation collapsing, the stale-row failure, the acceptance fixture, round-tripping).\n\n### The inventory — `scripts/hardcoded-language-allowlist.txt`\n\nSorted, tab-separated `<relative-path>\\t<canonical-literal-text>`, one row per literal, regenerated with `--write`. Seeded with today's debt (752 rows after the migration).\n\n### The burn-down, proven in this PR\n\n`src/engine_responses.rs` held per-intent English prose fallback constants that **duplicated** answers already present for all four languages in `data/seed/multilingual-responses.lino`. They are replaced by a single `cached_response(cell, intent, language)` helper that reads only from the seed via `seed::response_for`, degrading on the build-time-impossible parse failure to the intent slug (a meaning) — never to hardcoded prose. Regenerating the allowlist drops the 8 migrated rows — a clean burn-down diff (54 insertions, 99 deletions) in commit 2.\n\n### Wiring\n\n- `.github/workflows/release.yml`: new \"Check hardcoded natural language\" step in the lint job (verified running & green in CI).\n- `CONTRIBUTING.md`: added to the local-checks list.\n- `docs/design/no-hardcoded-natural-language.md`: documents the gate + burn-down loop.\n- `REQUIREMENTS.md`: R379 marked guarded.\n- `changelog.d/`: `bump: minor` fragment.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [x] **(a)** `rust-script scripts/check-hardcoded-language.rs` passes on the branch; inserting `\"Sorry, I can't do that.\"` into `src/` fails it with a `::error file=…::` annotation (verified live).\n- [x] **(b)** Allowlist committed, sorted, every row carries its file path.\n- [x] **(c)** CI job + `CONTRIBUTING.md` updated (the \"Check hardcoded natural language\" lint step ran green in CI).\n- [x] **(d)** At least one real allowlist entry migrated to seed data in the same PR (the 8 `engine_responses.rs` fallbacks) to prove the burn-down loop.\n\n## How to reproduce / verify\n\n```sh\n# passes on this branch\nrust-script scripts/check-hardcoded-language.rs\n\n# the gate's own inline tests (9)\nrust-script --test scripts/check-hardcoded-language.rs\n\n# fails when new prose is introduced in src/, then passes again after removing it\n# printf 'fn _x() -> &str { \"Sorry, I can'\\''t do that.\" }\\n' | cat - src/solver.rs  # demo\n```\n\n## Checks run locally\n\n- `cargo fmt --check` — clean\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features` — clean (exit 0)\n- `cargo test --test unit` — 1547 passed, 0 failed\n- gate + 9 inline tests — green\n- `origin/main` merged/rebased into the branch; full test tree compiles\n","created_at":"2026-07-14T06:15:28Z","updated_at":"2026-07-18T10:48:25Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":null,"assignees":[{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/othe